"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 1562, \"end\": 1571, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8452174013594466e-13, \"text\": \"Melbourne\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a strong contrast\", \"from\": 1480, \"to\": 1497}, {\"ngram\": \"the world's oldest biennale\", \"from\": 1531, \"to\": 1558}, {\"ngram\": \"its opening\", \"from\": 1651, \"to\": 1662}, {\"ngram\": \"stacked amps\", \"from\": 1668, \"to\": 1680}, {\"ngram\": \"discordant guitar riffs\", \"from\": 1682, \"to\": 1705}, {\"ngram\": \"a large LED screen\", \"from\": 1711, \"to\": 1729}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Among the chalked names in the Australian work is Moore's great-uncle, who accidentally killed his own father in a dispute over unpaid wages and spent nine months in Brisbane's Boggo Road Jail.\", \"from\": 1732, \"to\": 1925, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1763, \"end\": 1773, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\", \"score\": 0.8896328259429581, \"rank\": 0.12319973501285635, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\"}, {\"begin\": 1782, \"end\": 1787, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henry_Moore\", \"score\": 0.9822365548119621, \"rank\": 0.01808469161644211, \"text\": \"Moore\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henry_Moore\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henry_Moore\"}, {\"begin\": 1898, \"end\": 1906, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brisbane\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.7809839043375134e-13, \"text\": \"Brisbane\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brisbane\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brisbane\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the chalked names\", \"from\": 1738, \"to\": 1755}, {\"ngram\": \"his own father\", \"from\": 1827, \"to\": 1841}, {\"ngram\": \"a dispute\", \"from\": 1845, \"to\": 1854}, {\"ngram\": \"unpaid wages\", \"from\": 1860, \"to\": 1872}, {\"ngram\": \"nine months\", \"from\": 1883, \"to\": 1894}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The name of his great-grandmother Jane Clevin also appears.\", \"from\": 1927, \"to\": 1986, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1961, \"end\": 1965, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jane_Fonda\", \"score\": 0.6284437039486275, \"rank\": 0.5867721057992676, \"text\": \"Jane\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jane_Fonda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jane_Fonda\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The name\", \"from\": 1927, \"to\": 1935}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Samples of her hair and drawings were taken from her family by the anthropologist Norman Tindale when he visited Boggabilla in 1938.\", \"from\": 1987, \"to\": 2119, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2069, \"end\": 2083, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norman_Tindale\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Norman Tindale\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norman_Tindale\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norman_Tindale\"}, {\"begin\": 2100, \"end\": 2110, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boggabilla\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Boggabilla\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boggabilla\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boggabilla\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Samples\", \"from\": 1987, \"to\": 1994}, {\"ngram\": \"her hair\", \"from\": 1998, \"to\": 2006}, {\"ngram\": \"drawings\", \"from\": 2011, \"to\": 2019}, {\"ngram\": \"her family\", \"from\": 2036, \"to\": 2046}, {\"ngram\": \"the anthropologist\", \"from\": 2050, \"to\": 2068}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From that information Tindale mapped out a family tree in a Western anthropological fashion, Moore said.\", \"from\": 2121, \"to\": 2225, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2214, \"end\": 2219, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henry_Moore\", \"score\": 0.9822365548119621, \"rank\": 0.01808469161644211, \"text\": \"Moore\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henry_Moore\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henry_Moore\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that information\", \"from\": 2126, \"to\": 2142}, {\"ngram\": \"Tindale\", \"from\": 2143, \"to\": 2150}, {\"ngram\": \"a family tree\", \"from\": 2162, \"to\": 2175}, {\"ngram\": \"a Western anthropological fashion\", \"from\": 2179, \"to\": 2212}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It shows the comparison of the linear, Western idea of lineage, to the vast and complex relatedness of an Aboriginal kinship system.\\\"\", \"from\": 2226, \"to\": 2360, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2333, \"end\": 2343, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aboriginal_Australians\", \"score\": 0.9999999810875126, \"rank\": 1.891251367148405e-08, \"text\": \"Aboriginal\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aboriginal_Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aboriginal_Australians\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the comparison\", \"from\": 2236, \"to\": 2250}, {\"ngram\": \"the linear, Western idea\", \"from\": 2254, \"to\": 2278}, {\"ngram\": \"lineage\", \"from\": 2282, \"to\": 2289}, {\"ngram\": \"the vast and complex relatedness\", \"from\": 2294, \"to\": 2326}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Moore has left gaps - literal black holes - to represent massacres, the introduction of deadly diseases, and the destruction of cultural and linguistic knowledge.\", \"from\": 2362, \"to\": 2524, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Moore\", \"from\": 2362, \"to\": 2367}, {\"ngram\": \"gaps\", \"from\": 2377, \"to\": 2381}, {\"ngram\": \"literal black holes\", \"from\": 2384, \"to\": 2403}, {\"ngram\": \"massacres\", \"from\": 2419, \"to\": 2428}, {\"ngram\": \"the introduction\", \"from\": 2430, \"to\": 2446}, {\"ngram\": \"deadly diseases\", \"from\": 2450, \"to\": 2465}, {\"ngram\": \"the destruction\", \"from\": 2471, \"to\": 2486}, {\"ngram\": \"cultural and linguistic knowledge\", \"from\": 2490, \"to\": 2523}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The full scale of Moore's kith and kin inside the Australian Pavilion at the Venice Biennale.Credit:Andrea Rossetti/The Commercial The structure of his sprawling family tree upends the idea of there being original ancestors, an Adam and Eve in the Christian tradition.\", \"from\": 2526, \"to\": 2795, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2544, \"end\": 2549, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henry_Moore\", \"score\": 0.9822365548119621, \"rank\": 0.01808469161644211, \"text\": \"Moore\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henry_Moore\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henry_Moore\"}, {\"begin\": 2576, \"end\": 2586, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\", \"score\": 0.8896328259429581, \"rank\": 0.12319973501285635, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\"}, {\"begin\": 2633, \"end\": 2641, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dante_Gabriel_Rossetti\", \"score\": 0.9999989010145, \"rank\": 1.098986892460761e-06, \"text\": \"Rossetti\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dante_Gabriel_Rossetti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dante_Gabriel_Rossetti\"}, {\"begin\": 2775, \"end\": 2784, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9977539281747015, \"rank\": 0.0022511280161375837, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The full scale\", \"from\": 2526, \"to\": 2540}, {\"ngram\": \"kin\", \"from\": 2561, \"to\": 2564}, {\"ngram\": \"the Venice Biennale\", \"from\": 2599, \"to\": 2618}, {\"ngram\": \"Credit\", \"from\": 2619, \"to\": 2625}, {\"ngram\": \"The Commercial\", \"from\": 2642, \"to\": 2656}, {\"ngram\": \"his sprawling family tree\", \"from\": 2674, \"to\": 2699}, {\"ngram\": \"the idea\", \"from\": 2707, \"to\": 2715}, {\"ngram\": \"original ancestors\", \"from\": 2731, \"to\": 2749}, {\"ngram\": \"an Adam\", \"from\": 2751, \"to\": 2758}, {\"ngram\": \"Eve\", \"from\": 2763, \"to\": 2766}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There is no beginning to point to-rather Archie shows the vast abyss of time from which life springs,\\\" said curator Ellie Buttrose.\", \"from\": 2796, \"to\": 2928, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2838, \"end\": 2844, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archie_Comics\", \"score\": 0.9995487506796393, \"rank\": 0.00045145120974154305, \"text\": \"Archie\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archie_Comics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archie_Comics\"}, {\"begin\": 2913, \"end\": 2918, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ellie_Woodcomb\", \"score\": 0.9998963608644534, \"rank\": 0.00010364987754364721, \"text\": \"Ellie\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ellie_Woodcomb\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ellie_Woodcomb\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no beginning\", \"from\": 2806, \"to\": 2818}, {\"ngram\": \"the vast abyss\", \"from\": 2851, \"to\": 2865}, {\"ngram\": \"time\", \"from\": 2869, \"to\": 2873}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"By researching his family Archie demonstrates his connection to one of the longest-continuous cultures in the world and declares his sovereignty and the sovereignty of his people.\", \"from\": 2930, \"to\": 3110, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2957, \"end\": 2963, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archie_Comics\", \"score\": 0.9995487506796393, \"rank\": 0.00045145120974154305, \"text\": \"Archie\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archie_Comics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archie_Comics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his connection\", \"from\": 2977, \"to\": 2991}, {\"ngram\": \"the longest-continuous cultures\", \"from\": 3002, \"to\": 3033}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 3037, \"to\": 3046}, {\"ngram\": \"his sovereignty\", \"from\": 3060, \"to\": 3075}, {\"ngram\": \"the sovereignty\", \"from\": 3080, \"to\": 3095}, {\"ngram\": \"his people\", \"from\": 3099, \"to\": 3109}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By tracing back thousands of years he also shows how everyone on Earth has common ancestors, a reminder that we are all kin.\\\"\", \"from\": 3111, \"to\": 3236, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"thousands\", \"from\": 3127, \"to\": 3136}, {\"ngram\": \"years\", \"from\": 3140, \"to\": 3145}, {\"ngram\": \"everyone\", \"from\": 3164, \"to\": 3172}, {\"ngram\": \"Earth\", \"from\": 3176, \"to\": 3181}, {\"ngram\": \"common ancestors\", \"from\": 3186, \"to\": 3202}, {\"ngram\": \"a reminder\", \"from\": 3204, \"to\": 3214}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Among the many kinship names recorded inkith and kin,Moore also includes pejorative names given to Aboriginal people, sometimes appearing in media reports and official government correspondence, from picaninnie, to full blood, old Mary, and half-caste.\", \"from\": 3238, \"to\": 3490, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3291, \"end\": 3296, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henry_Moore\", \"score\": 0.9822365548119621, \"rank\": 0.01808469161644211, \"text